00:39:27,530 --> 00:39:32,750
who was trying to overpower the people, who were good.

508
00:39:33,970 --> 00:39:36,610
Shri Krishna

509
00:39:36,790 --> 00:39:40,210
said, "Now, what to do with this horrible fellow?"

510
00:39:40,410 --> 00:39:43,710
And this fellow had

511
00:39:43,890 --> 00:39:48,230
boons from Brahmadeva and from Mahadeva and everyone.

512
00:39:48,410 --> 00:39:51,410
So Shri Krishna is the center, after all,

513
00:39:51,610 --> 00:39:55,030
so He wanted to organize

514
00:39:55,230 --> 00:40:00,270
a proper destruction of this horrible rakshasa.

515
00:40:00,450 --> 00:40:03,310
So what he did, that

516
00:40:03,490 --> 00:40:08,550
there was a great right-sided saint

517
00:40:08,770 --> 00:40:15,270
meditating, and he had taken a boon

518
00:40:15,470 --> 00:40:18,390
that, "Nobody should disturb me.

519
00:40:18,570 --> 00:40:21,870
At least the one who disturbs me for the first time,

520
00:40:22,030 --> 00:40:26,830
I should have power to destroy, if I look at that person."

521
00:40:26,990 --> 00:40:32,150
And this one was meditating in a cave.

522
00:40:33,190 --> 00:40:36,990
Shri Krishna very beautifully ran away

523
00:40:37,150 --> 00:40:40,170
from the battlefield. His name is Ranchordas.

524
00:40:40,350 --> 00:40:45,570
It's little... little bit derogatory [PEOPLE?] to say to somebody

525
00:40:45,750 --> 00:40:49,770
that, "The one, who ran out of the battlefield."

526
00:40:49,950 --> 00:40:52,810
So Shri Krishna ran out of the battlefield.

527
00:40:52,990 --> 00:40:57,110
But there was no other way out to kill this horrible fellow.

528
00:40:57,330 --> 00:41:02,170
And he went, and he was covering Himself with a shawl.

529
00:41:02,350 --> 00:41:06,210
He went into that cave and

530
00:41:06,450 --> 00:41:09,850
covered that saint with His shawl.

531
00:41:10,030 --> 00:41:13,190
After Shri Krishna was running [away from] this horrible

532
00:41:13,370 --> 00:41:16,090
rakshasa to kill him,

533
00:41:16,270 --> 00:41:19,770
Shri Krishna went and hid Himself.

534
00:41:20,290 --> 00:41:23,250
When this rakshasa came near the cave,

535
00:41:23,450 --> 00:41:29,330
he saw the shawl covering this saint.

536
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:32,530
He said, "Oh, so now you are tired and sleeping here,

537
00:41:32,710 --> 00:41:36,650
running away from the field! Get up now!"

538
00:41:36,830 --> 00:41:41,310
As soon as he said this, this saint got up and looked at him.

539
00:41:41,490 --> 00:41:45,870
And he was completely burnt away.

540
00:41:49,130 --> 00:41:54,050
So, if Shri Krishna is the Virata at His Feet;

541
00:41:57,310 --> 00:42:02,990
or if Shri Krishna is Vitthala on His head,

542
00:42:03,190 --> 00:42:08,430
in between the two resides Hamsa chakra.

543
00:42:10,370 --> 00:42:16,210
The discretion is very beautifully described

544
00:42:16,430 --> 00:42:20,150
in the life of Shri Krishna.

545
00:42:20,430 --> 00:42:24,010
We can call Him that he had a naughty way of

546
00:42:24,190 --> 00:42:27,370
using his discretion.

547
00:42:29,970 --> 00:42:33,370
He has done so many things like that.

548
00:42:33,570 --> 00:42:38,010
But they create a drama. They create His Leela.

549
00:42:38,190 --> 00:42:41,170
Because He was Leela. That's why he could

550
00:42:41,350 --> 00:42:45,970
use His discretion to create a drama or a play.

551
00:42:46,710 --> 00:42:50,470
So on one side we have the help of Shri Krishna

552
00:42:50,650 --> 00:42:55,170
to give us the discretion, and on the other side we have Christ.

553
00:42:55,350 --> 00:42:58,330
In between is placed this Hamsa.

554
00:42:58,530 --> 00:43:02,290
So we have two great incarnations within us,

555
00:43:02,470 --> 00:43:07,570
who are the embodiment of discretion.

556
00:43:07,770 --> 00:43:11,650
So one side is Shri Krishna,

557
00:43:11,830 --> 00:43:14,930
who is the one,

558
00:43:15,090 --> 00:43:18,770
who looks after the conditioning side of it.

559
00:43:18,970 --> 00:43:21,790
And on the other side is Christ, who starts

560
00:43:21,970 --> 00:43:24,950
looking after the ego side of it.

561
00:43:25,130 --> 00:43:28,750
The One who says on the cross, "Oh, God, forgive them,

562
00:43:28,930 --> 00:43:32,270
because they do not know. Oh, Father, forgive them,

563
00:43:32,450 --> 00:43:35,670
for they do not know, what they are doing." Is the same One,

564
00:43:35,850 --> 00:43:39,830
who takes a hunter in his hand and hits people, starts beating them,

565
00:43:40,010 --> 00:43:43,570
because they are making money in the name of God.

566
00:43:43,790 --> 00:43:47,570
See the discretion. That's Jesus.

567
00:43:48,310 --> 00:43:53,090
Same Shri Krishna, who with his Sudarshan chakra

568
00:43:53,270 --> 00:43:59,350
can kill thousands and thousands of rakshasas,

569
00:43:59,630 --> 00:44:03,290
becomes the driver of Arjuna.

570
00:44:04,510 --> 00:44:09,250
The contrast of Their behavior

571
00:44:09,430 --> 00:44:14,970
is the beautiful saga of Their discretion.

572
00:44:15,990 --> 00:44:19,310
Now, for a Sahaja yogi it is important to understand

573
00:44:19,490 --> 00:44:22,530
that they have to work out their discretion

574
00:44:22,710 --> 00:44:26,670
in a manner that they develop their intuition.

575
00:44:27,310 --> 00:44:31,090
I would say the first thought could be the intuition,

576
00:44:31,270 --> 00:44:36,690
could be the intuition. "Could be that this is intuition."

577
00:44:36,870 --> 00:44:41,050
Try, experiment.

578
00:44:43,570 --> 00:44:47,810
But going to the extremes of everything is wrong in Sahaja yoga,

579
00:44:47,990 --> 00:44:51,590
you have to do everything in moderation.

580
00:44:51,770 --> 00:44:55,730
Like, I told them to see everything through vibrations.

581
00:44:55,910 --> 00:45:01,250
